    "breadcrumb": "OOP \u003e Testing",
    "description": "Content Note Much of the content in this chapter was adapted from Nathan Bean’s CIS 400 course at K-State, with the author’s permission. That content is licensed under a Creative Commons BY-NC-SA license.\nA critical part of the software development process is ensuring the software works! We mentioned earlier that it is possible to logically prove that software works by constructing a state transition table for the program, but once a program reaches a certain size, this strategy becomes less feasible. Similarly, it is possible to model a program mathematically and construct a theorem that proves it will perform as intended. But in practice, most software is validated through some form of testing. This chapter will discuss the process of testing object-oriented systems.",
