    "description": "The most important part of the book by the “Gang of Four,” as evidenced by the title, are the 23 software design patterns that are discussed within the book.\nA software design pattern is a reusable structure or solution to a common problem or usage within software development. Throughout the course of developing many different programs in the object-oriented paradigm, developers may find that they are reusing similar ideas or code structures within applications with completely different uses, which leads to the idea of formalizing these ideas into reusable structures.",
